President Donald J. Trump issued a proclamation expressing condolences for the victims of the shootings in El Paso, Texas, and Dayton, Ohio. The proclamation condemns the acts of violence and calls for unity with the affected communities. As a mark of respect, the President ordered that the flag of the United States be flown at half-staff at various locations until August 8, 2019. The proclamation was signed on August 4, 2019.